                        <condition>
                           <ab type="conservation">Dark brown papyrus of bad quality; rather thick and coarse; the papyrus is in bad condition; broken off at left, top and right; the lower margin is preserved; it has suffered damage, misaligned, wrinkled, removed and frayed fibers; several parts are covered with dark blots of dirt; a visible kollesis can be seen at the middle of recto and c.a. 5 cm from the right side of verso; many parts of the text have been either washed out or removed with the frayed fibers. Some horizontal fibers have been removed from top and bottom of verso.</ab>
                        </condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout>
                           <ab type="lines">recto: 24 lines; verso: 1 line</ab>
                           <ab type="recto-verso">Source of description: Recto + Verso</ab>
                        </layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     <p>Written along the fibers in black ink with thick nib; the letters are of medium-sized cursive; slow business hand; characterized by narrow theta; two loops beta; some times upsilon invades the interlinear spaces; the interlinear spaces are even of c.a. 0.5 cm; the text written in two columns; only the beginning of few lines are preserved in column 2; there are some abbreviations; no punctuation or other diacritical marks. Writing on verso are almost washed out and hard to read.</p>
                  </handDesc>
